{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I woke up in the middle of the night"},{"time":3000,"text":"with the sound of heavy explosion."},{"time":6000,"text":"It was deep at night."},{"time":8000,"text":"I do not remember what time it was."},{"time":10000,"text":"I just remember the sound"},{"time":12000,"text":"was so heavy"},{"time":14000,"text":"and so very shocking."},{"time":17000,"text":"Everything in my room was shaking --"},{"time":20000,"text":"my heart, my windows,"},{"time":23000,"text":"my bed, everything."},{"time":27000,"text":"I looked out the windows"},{"time":30000,"text":"and I saw a full half-circle"},{"time":33000,"text":"of explosion."},{"time":35000,"text":"I thought it was just like the movies,"},{"time":37000,"text":"but the movies had not conveyed them"},{"time":39000,"text":"in the powerful image that I was seeing"},{"time":42000,"text":"full of bright red"},{"time":44000,"text":"and orange and gray,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and a full circle of explosion."},{"time":48000,"text":"And I kept on staring at it"},{"time":51000,"text":"until it disappeared."},{"time":54000,"text":"I went back to my bed,"},{"time":57000,"text":"and I prayed,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and I secretly thanked God"},{"time":62000,"text":"that that missile"},{"time":64000,"text":"did not land on my family's home,"},{"time":68000,"text":"that it did not kill my family that night."},{"time":73000,"text":"Thirty years have passed,"},{"time":75000,"text":"and I still feel guilty about that prayer,"},{"time":79000,"text":"for the next day, I learned that that missile"},{"time":81000,"text":"landed on my brother's friend's home"},{"time":85000,"text":"and killed him"},{"time":88000,"text":"and his father,"},{"time":90000,"text":"but did not kill his mother or his sister."},{"time":96000,"text":"His mother showed up the next week"},{"time":98000,"text":"at my brother's classroom"},{"time":100000,"text":"and begged seven-year-old kids"},{"time":103000,"text":"to share with her any picture they may have"},{"time":106000,"text":"of her son,"},{"time":108000,"text":"for she had lost everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114000,"text":"This is not a story"},{"time":116000,"text":"of a nameless survivor of war,"},{"time":120000,"text":"and nameless refugees,"},{"time":122000,"text":"whose stereotypical images we see in our newspapers"},{"time":125000,"text":"and our TV"},{"time":128000,"text":"with tattered clothes,"},{"time":130000,"text":"dirty face, scared eyes."},{"time":134000,"text":"This is not a story of a nameless someone"},{"time":137000,"text":"who lived in some war,"},{"time":139000,"text":"who we do not know their hopes, their dreams,"},{"time":141000,"text":"their accomplishments, their families,"},{"time":144000,"text":"their beliefs, their values."},{"time":146000,"text":"This is my story."},{"time":150000,"text":"I was that girl."},{"time":154000,"text":"I am another image and vision"},{"time":157000,"text":"of another survivor of war."},{"time":160000,"text":"I am that refugee,"},{"time":162000,"text":"and I am that girl."},{"time":165000,"text":"You see,"},{"time":167000,"text":"I grew up in war-torn Iraq,"},{"time":171000,"text":"and I believe that there are two sides of wars"},{"time":174000,"text":"and we've only seen"},{"time":176000,"text":"one side of it."},{"time":178000,"text":"We only talk about"},{"time":180000,"text":"one side of it."},{"time":182000,"text":"But there's another side"},{"time":184000,"text":"that I have witnessed"},{"time":186000,"text":"as someone who lived in it"},{"time":188000,"text":"and someone who ended up working in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"I grew up with the colors of war --"},{"time":194000,"text":"the red colors of fire and blood,"},{"time":197000,"text":"the brown tones of earth"},{"time":200000,"text":"as it explodes"},{"time":202000,"text":"in our faces"},{"time":204000,"text":"and the piercing silver"},{"time":206000,"text":"of an exploded missile,"},{"time":208000,"text":"so bright"},{"time":210000,"text":"that nothing can protect your eyes from it."},{"time":214000,"text":"I grew up"},{"time":216000,"text":"with the sounds of war --"},{"time":218000,"text":"the staccato sounds of gunfire,"},{"time":221000,"text":"the wrenching booms of explosions,"},{"time":224000,"text":"ominous drones of jets flying overhead"},{"time":227000,"text":"and the wailing warning sounds"},{"time":229000,"text":"of sirens."},{"time":232000,"text":"These are the sounds you would expect,"},{"time":235000,"text":"but they are also the sounds"},{"time":237000,"text":"of dissonant concerts of a flock of birds"},{"time":240000,"text":"screeching in the night,"},{"time":242000,"text":"the high-pitched honest cries"},{"time":244000,"text":"of children"},{"time":246000,"text":"and the thunderous,"},{"time":248000,"text":"unbearable"},{"time":250000,"text":"silence."},{"time":253000,"text":"\"War,\" a friend of mine said,"},{"time":255000,"text":"\"is not about sound at all."},{"time":258000,"text":"It is actually about silence,"},{"time":261000,"text":"the silence of humanity.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":266000,"text":"I have since left Iraq"},{"time":269000,"text":"and founded a group called Women for Women International"},{"time":272000,"text":"that ends up working"},{"time":274000,"text":"with women survivors of wars."},{"time":277000,"text":"In my travels and in my work,"},{"time":279000,"text":"from Congo to Afghanistan,"},{"time":282000,"text":"from Sudan to Rwanda,"},{"time":284000,"text":"I have learned not only"},{"time":286000,"text":"that the colors and the sounds of war are the same,"},{"time":289000,"text":"but the fears of war are the same."},{"time":293000,"text":"You know, there is a fear of dying,"},{"time":295000,"text":"and do not believe any movie character"},{"time":298000,"text":"where the hero is not afraid."},{"time":300000,"text":"It is very scary"},{"time":302000,"text":"to go through that feeling"},{"time":304000,"text":"of \"I am about to die\""},{"time":306000,"text":"or \"I could die in this explosion.\""},{"time":309000,"text":"But there's also the fear"},{"time":311000,"text":"of losing loved ones,"},{"time":313000,"text":"and I think that's even worse."},{"time":315000,"text":"It's too painful. You don't want to think about it."},{"time":318000,"text":"But I think the worst kind of fear is the fear --"},{"time":322000,"text":"as Samia, a Bosnian woman, once told me,"},{"time":325000,"text":"who survived the four-years besiege of Sarajevo;"},{"time":328000,"text":"she said, \"The fear"},{"time":330000,"text":"of losing"},{"time":332000,"text":"the 'I' in me,"},{"time":334000,"text":"the fear of losing"},{"time":337000,"text":"the 'I' in me.\""},{"time":339000,"text":"That's what my mother in Iraq"},{"time":341000,"text":"used to tell me."},{"time":343000,"text":"It's like dying from inside-out."},{"time":347000,"text":"A Palestinian woman once told me,"},{"time":349000,"text":"\"It is not about the fear of one death,\""},{"time":352000,"text":"she said, \"sometimes I feel"},{"time":354000,"text":"I die 10 times in one day,\""},{"time":357000,"text":"as she was describing the marches of soldiers"},{"time":359000,"text":"and the sounds of their bullets."},{"time":361000,"text":"She said, \"But it's not fair,"},{"time":363000,"text":"because there is only one life,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and there should only be one death.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"We have been only seeing"},{"time":375000,"text":"one side of war."},{"time":377000,"text":"We have only been discussing and consumed"},{"time":380000,"text":"with high-level preoccupations"},{"time":382000,"text":"over troop levels, drawdown timelines,"},{"time":385000,"text":"surges and sting operations,"},{"time":387000,"text":"when we should be examining the details"},{"time":390000,"text":"of where the social fabric"},{"time":393000,"text":"has been most torn,"},{"time":396000,"text":"where the community has improvised"},{"time":398000,"text":"and survived"},{"time":400000,"text":"and shown acts of resilience"},{"time":402000,"text":"and amazing courage"},{"time":404000,"text":"just to keep life going."},{"time":408000,"text":"We have been so consumed"},{"time":411000,"text":"with seemingly objective discussions"},{"time":413000,"text":"of politics, tactics,"},{"time":415000,"text":"weapons, dollars"},{"time":417000,"text":"and casualties."},{"time":419000,"text":"This is the language"},{"time":421000,"text":"of sterility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"How casually"},{"time":426000,"text":"we treat casualties"},{"time":428000,"text":"in the context of this topic."},{"time":430000,"text":"This is where we conceive of rape and casualties"},{"time":433000,"text":"as inevitabilities."},{"time":436000,"text":"Eighty percent of refugees around the world"},{"time":439000,"text":"are women and children. Oh."},{"time":442000,"text":"Ninety percent of modern war casualties"},{"time":444000,"text":"are civilians."},{"time":446000,"text":"Seventy-five percent of them are women and children."},{"time":449000,"text":"How interesting."},{"time":452000,"text":"Oh, half a million women in Rwanda"},{"time":454000,"text":"get raped in 100 days."},{"time":456000,"text":"Or, as we speak now,"},{"time":459000,"text":"hundreds of thousands of Congolese women"},{"time":462000,"text":"are getting raped and mutilated."},{"time":464000,"text":"How interesting."},{"time":466000,"text":"These just become numbers that we refer to."},{"time":470000,"text":"The front of wars"},{"time":472000,"text":"is increasingly non-human eyes"},{"time":475000,"text":"peering down on our perceived enemies"},{"time":477000,"text":"from space,"},{"time":479000,"text":"guiding missiles toward unseen targets,"},{"time":482000,"text":"while the human conduct"},{"time":484000,"text":"of the orchestra of media relations"},{"time":486000,"text":"in the event that this particular drone attack"},{"time":489000,"text":"hits a villager"},{"time":491000,"text":"instead of an extremist."},{"time":493000,"text":"It is a chess game."},{"time":495000,"text":"You learn to play an international relations school"},{"time":498000,"text":"on your way out and up"},{"time":500000,"text":"to national and international leadership."},{"time":503000,"text":"Checkmate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"We are missing"},{"time":508000,"text":"a completely other side of wars."},{"time":512000,"text":"We are missing my mother's story,"},{"time":515000,"text":"who made sure with every siren, with every raid,"},{"time":518000,"text":"with every cut off-of electricity,"},{"time":520000,"text":"she played puppet shows for my brothers and I,"},{"time":522000,"text":"so we would not be scared"},{"time":524000,"text":"of the sounds of explosions."},{"time":526000,"text":"We are missing the story of Fareeda,"},{"time":529000,"text":"a music teacher,"},{"time":531000,"text":"a piano teacher, in Sarajevo,"},{"time":533000,"text":"who made sure"},{"time":535000,"text":"that she kept the music school open"},{"time":537000,"text":"every single day"},{"time":539000,"text":"in the four years of besiege in Sarajevo"},{"time":542000,"text":"and walked to that school,"},{"time":544000,"text":"despite the snipers shooting"},{"time":546000,"text":"at that school and at her,"},{"time":548000,"text":"and kept the piano, the violin, the cello"},{"time":551000,"text":"playing the whole duration of the war,"},{"time":554000,"text":"with students wearing their gloves and hats and coats."},{"time":557000,"text":"That was her fight."},{"time":559000,"text":"That was her resistance."},{"time":562000,"text":"We are missing the story of Nehia,"},{"time":565000,"text":"a Palestinian woman in Gaza"},{"time":567000,"text":"who, the minute there was a cease-fire in the last year's war,"},{"time":570000,"text":"she left out of home,"},{"time":572000,"text":"collected all the flour"},{"time":574000,"text":"and baked as much bread for every neighbor to have,"},{"time":577000,"text":"in case there is no cease-fire the day after."},{"time":581000,"text":"We are missing"},{"time":583000,"text":"the stories of Violet,"},{"time":585000,"text":"who, despite surviving genocide in the church massacre,"},{"time":588000,"text":"she kept on going on,"},{"time":590000,"text":"burying bodies, cleaning homes, cleaning the streets."},{"time":593000,"text":"We are missing stories of women"},{"time":596000,"text":"who are literally keeping life going"},{"time":599000,"text":"in the midst of wars."},{"time":601000,"text":"Do you know --"},{"time":603000,"text":"do you know that people fall in love in war"},{"time":606000,"text":"and go to school"},{"time":609000,"text":"and go to factories and hospitals"},{"time":611000,"text":"and get divorced and go dancing and go playing"},{"time":613000,"text":"and live life going?"},{"time":617000,"text":"And the ones who are keeping that life"},{"time":619000,"text":"are women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622000,"text":"There are two sides of war."},{"time":626000,"text":"There is a side that fights,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and there is a side that keeps the schools"},{"time":630000,"text":"and the factories and the hospitals open."},{"time":633000,"text":"There is a side that is focused on winning battles,"},{"time":636000,"text":"and there is a side that is focused"},{"time":638000,"text":"on winning life."},{"time":641000,"text":"There is a side that leads the front-line discussion,"},{"time":644000,"text":"and there is a side"},{"time":646000,"text":"that leads the back-line discussion."},{"time":649000,"text":"There is a side that thinks"},{"time":651000,"text":"that peace is the end of fighting,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and there is a side that thinks"},{"time":657000,"text":"that peace is the arrival"},{"time":659000,"text":"of schools and jobs."},{"time":662000,"text":"There is a side"},{"time":664000,"text":"that is led by men,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and there is a side"},{"time":668000,"text":"that is led by women."},{"time":670000,"text":"And in order for us to understand"},{"time":673000,"text":"how do we build lasting peace,"},{"time":676000,"text":"we must understand war and peace"},{"time":679000,"text":"from both sides."},{"time":681000,"text":"We must have a full picture"},{"time":683000,"text":"of what that means."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"In order for us to understand"},{"time":687000,"text":"what actually peace means,"},{"time":689000,"text":"we need to understand,"},{"time":691000,"text":"as one Sudanese woman once told me,"},{"time":693000,"text":"\"Peace is the fact that my toenails"},{"time":696000,"text":"are growing back again.\""},{"time":699000,"text":"She grew up in Sudan, in Southern Sudan,"},{"time":701000,"text":"for 20 years of war,"},{"time":703000,"text":"where it killed one million people"},{"time":706000,"text":"and displaced five million refugees."},{"time":709000,"text":"Many women were taken as slaves"},{"time":711000,"text":"by rebels and soldiers,"},{"time":713000,"text":"as sexual slaves who were forced also"},{"time":716000,"text":"to carry the ammunition and the water"},{"time":718000,"text":"and the food for the soldiers."},{"time":720000,"text":"So that woman walked for 20 years,"},{"time":723000,"text":"so she would not be kidnapped again."},{"time":726000,"text":"And only when there was some sort of peace,"},{"time":729000,"text":"her toenails grew back again."},{"time":733000,"text":"We need to understand peace"},{"time":735000,"text":"from a toenail's perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739000,"text":"We need to understand"},{"time":741000,"text":"that we cannot actually have negotiations"},{"time":743000,"text":"of ending of wars or peace"},{"time":745000,"text":"without fully including women"},{"time":748000,"text":"at the negotiating table."},{"time":750000,"text":"I find it amazing"},{"time":752000,"text":"that the only group of people"},{"time":754000,"text":"who are not fighting and not killing"},{"time":756000,"text":"and not pillaging and not burning and not raping,"},{"time":759000,"text":"and the group of people who are mostly --"},{"time":761000,"text":"though not exclusively --"},{"time":763000,"text":"who are keeping life going in the midst of war,"},{"time":766000,"text":"are not included in the negotiating table."},{"time":771000,"text":"And I do argue that women lead the back-line discussion,"},{"time":774000,"text":"but there are also men"},{"time":776000,"text":"who are excluded from that discussion."},{"time":778000,"text":"The doctors who are not fighting,"},{"time":780000,"text":"the artists, the students, the men who refuse to pick up the guns,"},{"time":783000,"text":"they are, too, excluded"},{"time":785000,"text":"from the negotiating tables."},{"time":788000,"text":"There is no way we can talk about a lasting peace,"},{"time":791000,"text":"building of democracy, sustainable economies,"},{"time":794000,"text":"any kind of stabilities,"},{"time":796000,"text":"if we do not fully include women"},{"time":799000,"text":"at the negotiating table."},{"time":801000,"text":"Not one, but 50 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"There is no way we can talk about the building of stability"},{"time":808000,"text":"if we don't start investing"},{"time":811000,"text":"in women and girls."},{"time":813000,"text":"Did you know"},{"time":815000,"text":"that one year"},{"time":817000,"text":"of the world's military spending"},{"time":819000,"text":"equals 700 years"},{"time":822000,"text":"of the U.N. budget"},{"time":825000,"text":"and equals 2,928 years"},{"time":828000,"text":"of the U.N. budget allocated for women?"},{"time":832000,"text":"If we just reverse"},{"time":834000,"text":"that distribution of funds,"},{"time":836000,"text":"perhaps we could have"},{"time":839000,"text":"a better lasting peace in this world."},{"time":842000,"text":"And last, but not least,"},{"time":844000,"text":"we need to invest in peace and women,"},{"time":847000,"text":"not only because it is the right thing to do,"},{"time":850000,"text":"not only because it is the right thing to do,"},{"time":853000,"text":"for all of us to build sustainable and lasting peace today,"},{"time":856000,"text":"but it is for the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859000,"text":"A Congolese woman,"},{"time":861000,"text":"who was telling me about"},{"time":863000,"text":"how her children saw their father killed in front of them"},{"time":866000,"text":"and saw her raped in front of them"},{"time":869000,"text":"and mutilated in front of them,"},{"time":871000,"text":"and her children saw their nine-year-old sibling"},{"time":873000,"text":"killed in front of them,"},{"time":876000,"text":"how they're doing okay right now."},{"time":879000,"text":"She got into Women for Women International's program."},{"time":881000,"text":"She got a support network."},{"time":883000,"text":"She learned about her rights."},{"time":885000,"text":"We taught her vocational and business skills. We helped her get a job."},{"time":888000,"text":"She was earning 450 dollars. She was doing okay."},{"time":891000,"text":"She was sending them to school. Have a new home."},{"time":893000,"text":"She said, \"But what I worry about the most"},{"time":896000,"text":"is not any of that."},{"time":898000,"text":"I worry that my children"},{"time":900000,"text":"have hate in their hearts,"},{"time":903000,"text":"and when they want to grow up, they want to fight again"},{"time":906000,"text":"the killers of their father and their brother.\""},{"time":910000,"text":"We need to invest in women,"},{"time":913000,"text":"because that's our only chance"},{"time":916000,"text":"to ensure that there is no more war"},{"time":918000,"text":"in the future."},{"time":920000,"text":"That mother has a better chance to heal her children"},{"time":923000,"text":"than any peace agreement can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927000,"text":"Are there good news? Of course, there are good news. There are lots of good news."},{"time":930000,"text":"To start with, these women that I told you about"},{"time":933000,"text":"are dancing and singing every single day,"},{"time":936000,"text":"and if they can,"},{"time":938000,"text":"who are we not to dance?"},{"time":940000,"text":"That girl that I told you about"},{"time":942000,"text":"ended up starting Women for Women International Group"},{"time":945000,"text":"that impacted one million people, sent 80 million dollars,"},{"time":948000,"text":"and I started this from zero,"},{"time":950000,"text":"nothing, nada, [unclear]."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":956000,"text":"They are women who are standing on their feet"},{"time":959000,"text":"in spite of their circumstances,"},{"time":962000,"text":"not because of it."},{"time":965000,"text":"Think of how the world can be a much better place"},{"time":968000,"text":"if, for a change,"},{"time":970000,"text":"we have a better equality,"},{"time":972000,"text":"we have equality,"},{"time":974000,"text":"we have a representation"},{"time":976000,"text":"and we understand war,"},{"time":978000,"text":"both from the front-line"},{"time":980000,"text":"and the back-line discussion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982000,"text":"Rumi, a 13th-century Sufi poet,"},{"time":985000,"text":"says, \"Out beyond the worlds"},{"time":987000,"text":"of right-doings and wrong-doings,"},{"time":990000,"text":"there is a field."},{"time":992000,"text":"I will meet you there."},{"time":994000,"text":"When the soul lies down in that grass,"},{"time":997000,"text":"the world is too full"},{"time":999000,"text":"to talk about."},{"time":1001000,"text":"Ideas, language,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"even the phrase 'each other'"},{"time":1005000,"text":"no longer makes any sense.\""},{"time":1009000,"text":"I humbly add -- humbly add --"},{"time":1012000,"text":"that out beyond"},{"time":1014000,"text":"the worlds of war and peace,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"there is a field,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"and there are many women and men"},{"time":1022000,"text":"[who] are meeting there."},{"time":1025000,"text":"Let us make this field a much bigger place."},{"time":1028000,"text":"Let us all meet in that field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1033000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}